All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AccountInterface
The AccountInterface class provides methods to handle user account settings and manage invite codes for users with additional privileges (like Managers).
Applicant
An applicant user in the BTO system.
ApplicantControl
The ApplicantControl class provides methods for handling actions that an applicant can perform, such as applying for projects, making enquiries, editing or deleting enquiries, and requesting withdrawal.
ApplicantInterface
The ApplicantInterface class provides a menu-driven interface for applicants to interact with the system.
Application
An application made by an applicant for a project.
ArrayControl
The ArrayControl class provides utility methods to handle lists of objects.
AuthControl
The AuthControl class handles user authentication, registration, and validation for different types of users (Manager, Officer, Applicant).
AuthInterface
The AuthInterface class provides a user interface for user authentication, including login and registration functionalities.
CustomSortControl
The CustomSortControl class provides functionality to allow users to customize the sorting of projects based on various attributes such as project name, location, total units available, and average price.
Data
A Data Transfer Object (DTO), or container, for data collections.
Enquiry
An enquiry made by an applicant regarding a project.
FlatBooking
A booking made by an applicant for a unit in a project.
Initialize
The Initialize class handles the initialization and saving of data to and from a binary file.
Manager
A manager user in the BTO system.
ManagerControl
The ManagerControl class manages functionalities for a Manager, such as creating, editing, deleting projects, and generating reports for projects.
ManagerInterface
The ManagerInterface class provides a user interface for a manager to manage projects, enquiries, applications, and withdrawal requests.
MaritalStatus
Enum representing the marital status of an individual.
Officer
An officer user in the BTO system.
OfficerControl
The OfficerControl class manages functionalities that are specific to officers, such as viewing registrations, registering for projects, and generating receipts for approved bookings.
OfficerInterface
The OfficerInterface class provides a user interface for officers to manage their assigned projects, handle applicants, manage enquiries, and confirm bookings.
Project
A project with various attributes, including information about units, applications, bookings, and more.
Registration
A registration of an officer to a project with a specific status.
Status
Enum representing the status of an application or registration.
Unit
A Unit that is available for sale, with attributes such as unit type, available units, and selling price.
UnitType
Enum representing different types of units.
User
Abstract class representing a user in the system.
Withdrawal
A Withdrawal request from an applicant, with the associated application, applicant, and status.
